NLP + Deep Learning (DL) means using Deep Learning algorithms to solve Natural Language Processing (NLP) problems.

Simple Definition
NLP (Natural Language Processing) = Helps computers understand, analyze, and generate human language (text or speech).
Deep Learning (DL) = A type of Machine Learning that uses neural networks with many layers to learn complex patterns automatically.

NLP + DL = Teaching computers to understand language using deep neural networks.


============

Real-Life Example
Example: Gmail Spam Detection

Input:

Congratulations! You won ₹50,000. Click here.
Traditional NLP + ML
Clean the text
Convert text into numbers (Bag of Words, TF-IDF)
Train a model like Naive Bayes or SVM
Predict Spam
Text
   ↓
Preprocessing
   ↓
TF-IDF
   ↓
Naive Bayes
   ↓
Spam
NLP + Deep Learning

The model automatically learns important words and their meanings.

Text
   ↓
Embedding Layer
   ↓
LSTM / GRU / Transformer
   ↓
Dense Layer
   ↓
Spam / Not Spam

No need to manually create many features.

Why Use Deep Learning in NLP?

Traditional ML struggles to understand:

Word meaning
Context
Sentence order
Grammar

Deep Learning understands all of these much better.

Example:

Sentence 1:

I went to the bank to deposit money.

Sentence 2:

I sat on the bank of the river.

Traditional ML:

Bank = Same word

Deep Learning:

Sentence 1 → Financial bank
Sentence 2 → River bank

It understands the context.

